 fitting for our times. Then, in light of the book's thesis, Gellman offers his understanding of Torah from Heaven, prayer, and the continuing validity of the commandments, for present-day traditional Judaism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 7aRELIGION / Judaism / Sacred Writings.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertASP eBook Package 2016z978311068816040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781618115201423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781618115201.jpg  a978-3-11-068816-0  ASP eBook Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK